# Project Structure

This is a web application for managing product categories with a hierarchical structure. The application follows a client-server architecture with a FastAPI backend and a modern frontend using Tailwind CSS.

## Core Components

### Frontend
- `templates/index.html`: Main application interface
  - Uses Tailwind CSS for styling
  - Implements a responsive layout with sidebar and main content area
  - Handles category management UI and interactions

### Backend
- `app.py`: Main FastAPI application
  - Defines API endpoints for product and category management
  - Handles database operations and business logic

### Database
- Uses SQLite for data storage
- Tables:
  - `products`: Stores product information
  - `categories`: Stores category hierarchy
  - `product_categories`: Maps products to categories

## Key Features
- Product selection and management
- Three-level category hierarchy
- Category creation and assignment
- CSV export functionality
- Real-time updates and notifications

## Development Guidelines
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Use type hints for all functions
- Implement comprehensive error handling
- Maintain clear separation of concerns
- Document all API endpoints
